r":"Morningstar","reportDate":"2026-06-12T22:54:03Z","reportTitle":"Adobe provides content creation, document management, and digital marketing and advertising software and services to creative professionals and marketers for creating, managing, delivering, measuring, optimizing, and engaging with compelling content multiple operating systems, devices, and media. The company operates with three segments: digital media content creation, digital experience for marketing solutions, and publishing for legacy products (less than 5% of revenue). ","reportType":"Analyst Report","targetPrice":380.0,"targetPriceStatus":"Maintained"},{"headline":"Analyst Report: Applied Materials, Inc.","id":"MS_0P000000H9_AnalystReport_1781304794000","investmentRating":"Bearish","provider":"Morningstar","reportDate":"2026-06-12T22:53:14Z","reportTitle":"Applied Materials is the largest semiconductor wafer fabrication equipment manufacturer in the world. It has a broad portfolio spanning nearly every corner of the WFE ecosystem. Applied Materials holds leading market share in deposition, which entails the layering of new materials on semiconductor wafers. It is more exposed to general-purpose logic chips made at integrated device manufacturers and foundries. It counts the largest chipmakers in the world as customers, including TSMC, Intel, and Samsung. ","reportType":"Analyst Report","targetPrice":470.0,"targetPriceStatus":"Maintained"},{"headline":"Analyst Report: Keysight Technologies, Inc.","id":"MS_0P00014HI6_AnalystReport_1781304058000","investmentRating":"Bearish","provider":"Morningstar","reportDate":"2026-06-12T22:40:58Z","reportTitle":"Keysight Technologies is a leader in the field of testing and measurement, helping electronics OEMs and suppliers alike bring products to market to fit industry standards and specifications. Keysight specializes in the communications market, but also supplies into the government, automotive, industrial, and semiconductor manufacturing markets. Keysight’s solutions include testing tools, analytical software, and services. The firm’s stated objective is to reduce time to market and improve efficiency at its more than 30,000 customers. ","reportType":"Analyst Report","targetPrice":250.0,"targetPriceStatus":"Maintained"}],"symbol":"^YH311","topCompanies":[{"dayChangePercent":0.001562,"lastPrice":205.19,"marketCap":5204124074783.0,"marketWeight":0.18802594,"name":"NVIDIA Corporation","rating":"Strong Buy","symbol":"NVDA","targetPrice":298.932,"ytdReturn":0.1002},{"dayChangePercent":-0.0152217,"lastPrice":291.13,"marketCap":4528552278262.0,"marketWeight":0.1636174,"name":"Apple Inc.","rating":"Buy","symbol":"AAPL","targetPrice":312.716,"ytdReturn":0.0709},{"dayChangePercent":0.00102473,"lastPrice":390.74,"marketCap":3090451680837.0,"marketWeight":0.11165857,"name":"Microsoft Corporation","rating":"Strong Buy","symbol":"MSFT","targetPrice":561.388,"ytdReturn":-0.1921},{"dayChangePercent":-0.00907747,"lastPrice":382.07,"marketCap":1998077366566.0,"marketWeight":0.072190896,"name":"Broadcom Inc.","rating":"Strong Buy","symbol":"AVGO","targetPrice":522.062,"ytdReturn":0.1039},{"dayChangePercent":-0.014319148,"lastPrice":981.61,"marketCap":1010404625113.0,"marketWeight":0.0365061,"name":"Micron Technology, Inc.","rating":"Strong Buy","symbol":"MU","targetPrice":828.725,"ytdReturn":2.4393},{"dayChangePercent":0.0473334,"lastPrice":511.57,"marketCap":821643379871.0,"marketWeight":0.029686123,"name":"Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.","rating":"Strong Buy","symbol":"AMD","targetPrice":486.333,"ytdReturn":1.3887},{"dayChangePercent":0.065065,"lastPrice":124.57,"marketCap":620811503128.0,"marketWeight":0.02243003,"name":"Intel Corporation","rating":"Hold","symbol":"INTC","targetPrice":93.1171,"ytdReturn":2.3759},{"dayChangePercent":0.00016294800000000005,"lastPrice":184.13,"marketCap":555249433738.0,"marketWeight":0.020061262,"name":"Oracle Corporation","rating":"Buy","symbol":"ORCL","targetPrice":255.384,"ytdReturn":-0.0553},{"dayCh